Umuahia – Commandant of the Nigerian Navy College of Accounts and Finance, Owerrinta, Abia State, Commodore Usman Bala, has tasked Nigerians on the need to assist Nigeria’s security agencies to combat the current insecurity across the country by being vigilant within their locality. The Naval Commandant made the call when he received the delegation from the Adventist Men’s Organisation of the Seventh Day Adventist Church who paid him a courtesy visit in his office. Commodore Bala said he was not competent to speak on security but commended the Adventist men for their roles in propagating the gospel of Jesus Christ. -Advertisement- He urged Nigerians to play their roles in securing lives and properties and not leaving it alone to the security agents. The Naval Commandant advised the Church to always use its programmes and sermons to admonish and to eschew violence for maintenance of peace in the South-East and the nation as a whole. He promised to give the men’s fellowship security cover during their convention.